node.text:
FULL video in Bio 🤙🏾🤙🏾 
What a treat it was to spend so much time on the north shore this year and score some pumping waves. Thanks to everyone for sharing the waves, clips, and @ryanperry for the edit 🤘🏾🤘🏾 #northshore #hawaii #surfing #connercoffin #grateful

node.text:
Down days on the north shore playing music! I’ve been into music and surfing since I was a little kid in a lot of ways from my dad turning me onto both. Music has been a super good creative outlet and feels super similar to surfing. Thanks for the down day video @peterkingphoto / @jamhouseofficial 
#transacoustic

node.text: I wrote this song a while back, but it feels particularly relevant right now during these bizarre times of covid-19 and self isolation. I’ve never shared songs that I’ve written, but am excited to take this time to work on existing pieces and write new music. ✌🏽 and ❤️

node.text: Just finished reading a book about the allman brothers which turned me on to this old carter family Tune that they used to jam. Was really really sad to hear about Neal Casal passing this week, so this ones for him. An amazing player who carried the torch of the music I love and was an even better person that seemed to have such a positive influence on people around him. If you’re struggling on the inside reach out to a friend or someone for a helping hand 🙌🏽🙌🏽❤️❤️

node.text:
#flashbackfriday. Volcom pipe pro 10 point ride 2019. Pipe was firing all day and I was the last heat of the day. The swell was turning north just a few heats before mine and it started to get funky. Rain was pouring, wind went cross shore, and the current moved through the line up. I paddled out and was looking for rights. Koa smith was deeper in the line up than me and we were scratching out to this wave. I thought he was going to whip it and go, but when I looked back he was still paddling over. I whipped it without Really realizing how deep I was but it was too late to pull back. I thought I was going to eat shit on the drop but when my fins grabbed at the bottom I knew I had a chance. I wrestled the foam ball, felt it spit, but then saw it pinch. I thought I was done, but tried to punch through. It worked out and I got a 10 point ride. Pipeline rules and I look forward to surfing there soon. Vid @ryanperry 
#pipeline #10 #wsl #connercoffin #northshore #oahu #tube

node.text:
#singleclipsunday ! Surfed for 6 hours this day with my dad, brother, and friends. The morning session the tide was low and the waves a bit better. This was the post lunch, post siesta session. Mostly just locals out that were ripping. We picked off a few scraps. The high tide actually made for some super fun rides with a nice onshore coping wind. I surfed till paddling hurt before heading back to the hammock. Mexico 🇲🇽 🤘🏾👍🏾🍻👌🏾
Video @ryanperry #connercoffin #mexico #surfing #waves #gracias #powersurfing #combo #carve #layback #grateful

node.text:
#flashbackfriday to one of my favorite rides from the north shore last year. It was a new swell and pipe was funky. I rode the bike to sunset and paddled out on a 6’8” that was one of @joelparko ‘s old favorites. It was just the right amount of west and north to have big wedges from deep and some rolling into the inside bowl. Some of the best sunset I’d ever seen. Good waves everywhere. Good surfers everywhere too. All of the boys and girls warming up for the sunset contest and all of the best locals on the north shore. I caught a few bits and pieces but wasn’t finding much in the crowd. I decided to try my luck up towards the point and hopefully not get caught by a big west peak. I found myself paddling into this wedging double up. Feeling like I dodged a barrel and with more speed than ever, I tried to get up real high and extend a carve all the way down the wave. After this turn the wave shut down. I pulled through the back and my board broke. I swam in and rode home. 
I think this is @ryanmackphoto photo?
#sunset #northshore #hawaii #speed #carve #connercoffin #surfing #power #grateful #powersurfing #fun #jsindustries #letsgo
